Searching for alternatives in cities
Conservatives argued that the root of the problem in cities was the migration of specially protected hamlets, indicating that the use of chemicals in agriculture was increasingly destroying traditional habitats.
Hunting, expanding construction and cutting down traditional nesting trees made life difficult for birds.
The crows are under guard.
