Fujimori was hospitalized again for medical examination.
Former President Alberto Fujimori was hospitalized in a state hospital on Tuesday to be examined for muscle loss in his legs, his family doctor said.
Fujimori, 72, who has been sentenced to 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed during his reign (1990-2000), suffers from several diseases, including tongue cancer, for which he has been operated on four times and is under observation.
